        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-04T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-04T20:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Service, Richard M.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spiker</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-05T10:00:00+09:00">September 5, 1947—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 5—1:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Service returned yesterday evening reporting continuing negotiations by Navy
                    at Goose Point. Details will be sent later message following receipt today’s
                    report from negotiators.</p>
                <pb facs="0987" n="977" xml:id="pg_977"/>
                <p>Sent Embassy 101; repeated Department 76.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spiker</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
